I don't know if you could do this using ReadMem and WriteMem (should
be able to, theoretically) but try writing a string such as this to a
savefile character by character:

PLAYERNAME=GazChap

So you'd write each character in turn and then a line feed (Chr$(10))
to the file.

Then you can read in, character by character, everything up to a line
feed and you'd have the string.

Now you just have to extract the bit before the equals (in this case
PLAYERNAME) and the bit after the equals (GazChap), compare the bit
before (PLAYERNAME) to your list of variables to find out where it
goes, and then set that variable to the bit after (GazChap).

