On 26 Oct 2002 at 15:25, Joar Berntsen wrote:

> I wanted to use shapes beyond 1000,
> and I have set max number high enough,
> but my entire system freezes
> when I try to GetaShape into anywhere about 1024
> and beyond

Sounds like the assembly code that Blitz creates to calculate the address of an object is 
broken for this case:

shape number * sizeof.shape = 1024 * 32 = 32768

It seems likely that the Blitz code would use a word offset from an address register to 
calculate the address of the shape object. This word offset would be treated as a negative 
value by the CPU, causing the wrong address to be passed to GetAShape and would mean 
getashape would overwrite some memory that it should not.

Nothing you can do about that unless Bernd fixes it. If that really is the problem :)

