The problem is that string constants are not inserted at
th beginning of the executable even if
you type them at the begining. The librarie
code is inserted first. So if one of the
blitz libraries contains a version string this one will
be found instead of yours. This also means
your version string is found slower in larger executables,
but of course this works too if you dont use such a library.

Ciao,

Thilo
 

