Subject: @{b}Printing Problems - solved@{ub}

Hi there,

If anyone has followed the thread regarding my printing problems - I've solved
it, and thought I'd share.

To recap - I recently installed a Micronik Z2 board and CV64/3D. Since then,
Wordworth and Drawstudion have produced printouts that appeared "Smeared",
although other applications have printed fine.

Additional information:- The CV64/3D has no scandoubler. This appears to be
significant. Since I have no scandoubler, then at the moment, the Video slot
enabler on the Micronik board is redundant. As a last ditch attempt at solving
this, I removed it. Printing problems solved.

I don't know why only a couple of applications should have been affected, but
that's Amiga life.

I dare say that, as and when I get a scandoubler, th problem may recur (tho'
since I will have further H/W it may not), but I'll quit worrying about it 'til
then.

