@NODE "mail_116" " Re: textfit_ problems now :( "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 10-23-02 21:43:50
Subject: @{b}Re: textfit_ problems now :(@{ub}

>   char.l=TextFit_(rp,&text$,textlen,*TE,0,1,width,fontheight)

Try:

DefType.TextExtent TE
char.l=TextFit_(rp,&text$,textlen,&TE,0,1,width,fontheight)

TextFit fills in that text extent, so you obviously need to give it some space to store the result. 
Since you need to provide the space, you must create a variable for it, not point elsewhere.

(General advice)
Remember that things that are pointed to should match up. Even if you were using the second 
TextExtent (the on you set to 0), which is the one where you can specify a size into which the text 
must fit, it is a pointer to a TextExtent not a RastPort.

